        <div xml:id="AN15-kilavi"></div>
        <div xml:id="AN15">
            <lg type="edition"><l>emveṅ kāma miyaiva tāyiṉ</l>
<l><choice><seg>meymmali</seg><seg>meymali</seg></choice> perumpūṭ cemmaṟ kōcar</l>
<l>kommaiyam pacuṅkāyk kuṭumi viḷainta</l>
<l>pāka lārkaip paṟaikkaṭ pīlit</l>
<l>tōkaik kāviṟ ṟuḷunā ṭaṉṉa</l>
<l>vaṟuṅkai vampalart tāṅkum paṇpiṟ</l>
<l>ceṟinta cēric cemmaṉ mūtū</l>
<l>raṟinta mākkaṭ ṭākuka tilla</l>
<l>tōḻi <choice><seg>mārum</seg><seg>māru</seg></choice> <choice><seg>yāṉum</seg><seg>nāṉum</seg></choice> pulampac</l>
<l>cūḻi yāṉaic cuṭarppū ṇaṉṉa<supplied>ṉ</supplied></l>
<l>pāḻi yaṉṉa kaṭiyuṭai viyaṉakarc</l>
<l>ceṟinta kāppikan tavaṉoṭu <choice><seg>pōki</seg><seg>poruntiya</seg></choice></l>
<l><choice><seg>yatta</seg><seg>vatta</seg></choice> viruppai yārkaḻal putuppūt</l>
<l>tuytta vāya tukaṇilam <choice><seg>pārppak</seg><seg>parappik</seg></choice></l>
<l>koṉṟai yañciṉaik kuḻaṟpaḻaṅ <choice><seg>koḻuti</seg><seg>koḻutiya</seg></choice></l>
<l>vaṉkai yeṇkiṉ vayanirai parakku</l>
<l>miṉṟuṇaip <choice><seg>payanta</seg><seg>paṭarnta</seg></choice> koḷkaiyō ṭōrāṅkuk</l>
<l>kuṉṟa vēyiṟ ṟiraṇṭaveṉ</l>
<l><choice><seg>meṉṟō<supplied>ṇ</supplied></seg><seg>meṉṟō</seg></choice> <choice><seg>maññai</seg><seg>ḷaññai</seg></choice> ceṉṟa vāṟē.</l></lg>
            <lg type="translation" xml:lang="en">
<l>If our hot desire is agreeable,</l>
<l>let there be many people who know,<note place="foot">Literally: “let the way be one with people who know”</note></l>
<l rend="indent">	in the upright old village with tight-packed quarters</l>
<l rend="indent">	of a kind that gives shelter to empty-handed strangers,</l>
<l rend="indent">	like the Tuḷu land, with forests of peacocks</l>
<l rend="indent">	with drum-eyed tail feathers, becoming full of the jack-fruit</l>
<l rend="indent">	cultivated on top as round green unripe fruit</l>
<l rend="indent">	by the upright Kōcar with big ornaments, rejoicing in the truth,</l>
<l>– the way my <choice><seg>peacock </seg><seg>mother(?)<note place="foot">Thus the second strand, followed by all the paper manuscripts and confirmed by the old commentary. Could this be a reference to the fact that the girl is pregnant?</note> </seg></choice> with soft shoulders has gone,</l>
<l>that have grown round like hill bamboo,</l>
<l rend="indent">	as <choice><seg>if </seg><seg>one </seg></choice> with the maxim of <choice><seg>producing a </seg><seg>setting out for the </seg></choice> pleasing companion,</l>
<l rend="indent">	where strong packs of strong-clawed bears spread,</l>
<l><choice><seg>	having </seg><seg>	who </seg></choice> culled out the <choice><seg>flute[-like] </seg><seg>flute </seg></choice> fruits on the pretty branches of the Laburnum,</l>
<l><choice><seg>	so as to peer </seg><seg>	fanning </seg></choice> out over the dusty ground, with mouths that have tasted</l>
<l rend="indent">	the new flowers loosened <choice><seg>on </seg><seg>at </seg></choice> the stems of the Mahua trees by the road,</l>
<l><choice><seg>[she who] went </seg><seg>so as to get together </seg></choice> with him, bypassing the tight watch</l>
<l rend="indent">	on the wide mansion well-protected like Pāḻi</l>
<l rend="indent">	of Naṉṉaṉ with glowing ornaments [and] elephants with decked fronts,</l>
<l rend="indent">	so that [her] friends and me are lonely.</l></lg>
        </div>
    </body>
